"n. 止痛药 【英】 n. 止痛药(anything that relieves pain or soothes) 【记】 an+odyne(痛)→不痛 →止痛药 n. 止痛药(如阿斯匹林) = analgesic = anesthetic 【记】1)an非, 不, odyne痛－使不痛－止痛药2)读: 爱脑袋. 要问止痛药最爱谁, 脑袋和牙有一拼. 不过统计结果显示, 头痛患者人数和用药频率更胜一筹. 所以, 止痛药爱脑袋. 【记】音：安脑定，安宁定，就是安定(一种药)，“安脑定痛”是种止头痛的药；音：阿诺德(史瓦辛格)不知疼痛，打不死； a + no不 + dyn 死→不死→止痛 anodyne (adj.)  1540s, from Medieval Latin anodynus ""pain-removing, allaying pain,"" from Latin anodynus ""painless,"" from Greek anodynos ""free from pain,"" from an- ""without"" (see an- (1)) + odyne ""pain,"" a word perhaps from PIE root *ed- ""to eat"" (source of Lithuanian edžioti ""to devour, bite,"" edžiotis ""to suffer pain;"" see eat). In old slang, frequently a euphemism for ""death;"" as in anodyne necklace ""hangman's noose."""
